  "prompt": "How is the M27 IAR issued at the US Marines squad level? One for each fire-team, or mixed with the M249 SAW?",
  "response": "The M27 Infantry Automatic Rifle (IAR) is typically issued at the squad level in the U.S. Marine Corps as a replacement for the M249 Squad Automatic Weapon (SAW). The standard configuration usually includes one M27 IAR per fire team within a squad, meaning that for a standard Marine rifle squad, which comprises three fire teams, you would typically find three M27s (one per fire team).\n\nThe M249 SAW is being phased out in favor of the M27 IAR, which is intended to provide a more versatile and effective automatic weapon for infantry operations. The M27 offers improved accuracy and weight advantages over the M249, and it is designed to be used primarily by the designated automatic rifleman in each fire team.\n\nHowever, there might be variations depending on specific units and operational requirements, but the general trend is to maximize the use of the M27 IAR across squads.",
